The tablet is badly preserved and very fragmentary. Legible are the names of <strong>A</strong>, <strong>B </strong>and the slave (<em>qallu</em>) <strong>C</strong>. Further the tablet mentions, 0;1.0 kor of pure salt (<em>ṭābtu ellu</em>), 0;1.0 kor of cress seed (<em>sahl&ucirc;</em>), (amount broken) of <em>abah&scaron;innu</em>-stalks (<em>abah&scaron;innu</em>), 0;1.4 kor flour (<em>qēmu</em>), in payment for the <em>rikis qabli</em> service (<em>rikis qabli</em>) of the x<sup>th</sup> year of Darius, the fixed rent (<em>sūtu</em>) of <strong>B</strong> and the slave <strong>C</strong> acting as proxy for (<em>ina na&scaron;parti</em>) 2 persons whose names are broken. Fragmentary list of witnesses and the scribe: Nidinti-Bēl/Nab&ucirc;-ina-t&ecirc;&scaron;ē-<em>ēṭir</em>//&Scaron;a-nā&scaron;i&scaron;u.<br />
